WEBVTT

00:00.300 --> 00:03.934
Quorum — the Nonprofit Board OS.

00:04.234 --> 00:13.724
Stage one is short, but mighty: form the corporation, and get its tax ID. Open your
Launch Checklist and follow along.

00:14.024 --> 00:31.506
Step one: file the Articles of Incorporation with the California Secretary of State. You
do it online, through their bizfile system. When it's approved, you get back a stamped
copy — that's the foundation's birth certificate. Save it forever.

00:31.806 --> 00:43.504
Step two: get the foundation's E I N — its free federal tax ID — at IRS dot gov. The
online form takes about ten minutes, and you receive the number right away.

00:43.804 --> 00:56.462
The order matters: the E I N comes after the Articles — and later, the bank will ask to
see both. Notice ours are checked off and crossed out. Done, and done.

00:56.762 --> 01:06.324
That's stage one — the foundation legally exists. Next: the big one. The organizational
board meeting.
